## Phase C: DuckDB Analytics Layer ✅

### New Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [duckdb_analytics_adapter.py](file:///d:/cell/Morphosphere_v37_0_native_runtime_prototype_flat_complete.tar/Morphosphere_v37_0_native_runtime_prototype_flat_complete/Morphosphere_v37_0_native_runtime_prototype_flat_complete/morphosphere_v2pp/engines/duckdb_analytics_adapter.py) | Dual-backend: SQLite (write) + DuckDB (read/analytics) |

### Architecture Decision

```
WRITE PATH:  Application → SQLite (unchanged, backward compatible)
READ PATH:   Analytics → DuckDB → sqlite_scanner → SQLite file (zero-copy)
```

> [!NOTE]
> We chose a dual-backend strategy over full migration because SQLite has 100+ touchpoints.
> DuckDB reads SQLite files directly via `sqlite_scanner` — zero data duplication.

Features:
- `query()` / `aggregate_query()` — columnar analytics on SQLite data
- `export_parquet()` — export to Parquet for external tools
- `benchmark_vs_sqlite()` — automated performance comparison
- Lock-free concurrent reads during spike data ingestion

